Transform this existing Python ebook scraping and generation repository into a production-ready digital library web application.

Read the repository first and base the implementation on what already exists instead of replacing it blindly.

Repository reality you must account for
- This repository is currently a script-based scraper/generator, not a web app.
- `code/main.py` batch-processes static `BOOK_URLS` from `code/config.py`, but this repository currently only includes `code/config.example.py`, so configuration/bootstrap needs cleanup during the refactor.
- `code/scraper.py` is the core scraping layer. It already contains useful logic for:
  - HTTP fetching with retries
  - title normalization and fuzzy duplicate-friendly matching
  - dedication/book-info extraction
  - lesson/topic discovery and TOC building
  - source-page scraping from `ebanglalibrary.com`
- `scrape_book_data()` currently returns a dictionary shaped around fields like:
  - `book_title`
  - `author`
  - `series`
  - `book_type`
  - `cover`
  - `main_content`
  - `book_info`
  - `dedication`
  - `toc`
  - `content_items`
  - `output_folder`
- `code/html_book.py` generates a standalone `book.html`.
- `code/epub_book.py` and `code/epub_properties/` generate the EPUB output and page templates.
- The current HTML and EPUB generators assume single-string values for fields like author/series/type, so they must be adapted carefully to support normalized relational metadata without breaking output generation.
- Generated files are currently written under `outputs/<book_name>/`.
- `code/config.example.py` is only a placeholder config file.
- There are current implementation inconsistencies to fix during refactor, for example `code/main.py` reads `data.get('title')` even though the scraper returns `book_title`.
- The repo currently has no Django project, no React frontend, no database models, no tests, and no README-based product documentation.

Main objective
Keep the existing scraping and book-generation capability, but evolve the repository into a secure, resumable, production-ready digital library platform with:
- Django + PostgreSQL backend
- React frontend
- persistent storage for books, submissions, metadata, generated assets, and permissions
- authenticated submission and management workflows
- controlled read/download access
- EPUB generation and reader launch integration
- a premium library-first UI
- clear documentation, tests, and resumable implementation phases

Critical product framing
- This is a digital library/catalog product first, not a full e-reader product.
- Reading exists, but it is secondary to submission, storage, management, discovery, permissions, and controlled distribution.
- Broad submission is important. In Phase 1, this can be satisfied through self-service accounts plus a submitter role. If guest submission is added later, it must be heavily protected against abuse.
- Every accepted submission attempt must be saved in the database, even if it later matches an existing book, fails to process, or requires review.
- The source site for ingestion is only `https://www.ebanglalibrary.com/`.
- LLM integration is explicitly deferred. Preserve data/provenance so AI-assisted extraction can be added later without redesigning the system.

